{"type":"message","id":"9e89cf6f","parentId":"f17845f6","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:26:33.201Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4ahp48l1fst3_1","toolName":"image","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This image is a screenshot of a Linux terminal window showing the output of the command `openclaw channels list`. The user is `halei` on a machine named `Surface-Pro-4`.\n\nThe output displays information about **OpenClaw** version 2026.3.31, including several plugin loading messages and the status of configured channels and authentication providers.\n\n### Chat Channels\nThe output lists three chat channels and their status:\n*   **Feishu tts:** configured, enabled\n*   **openclaw-weixin 2be069d50844-im-bot:** configured, enabled\n*   **OpenClawWeChat default:** not configured, enabled\n\n### Auth Providers (OAuth + API keys)\nTwo authentication providers are listed:\n*   **openrouter:default** (using an api_key)\n*   **minimax:cn** (using an api_key)\n\n### Other Details\n*   **Plugins:** Several plugins are being loaded, including `lcm` (using a MiniMax model), `memory-lancedb-pro` (using an OpenAI embedding model), and `session-strategy`.\n*   **Usage:** There is a usage summary for **MiniMax**, showing 11% left on a 5-hour limit, which resets in 34 minutes.\n*   **Environment:** The file paths indicate the software is installed in the `/home/halei/.openclaw/` directory."}],"details":{"model":"minimax/MiniMax-VL-01","image":"/home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/2e8897cc-849e-46a7-819a-79f3fefdca9c.jpg","attempts":[]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775057193196}}
{"type":"message","id":"29b14f62","parentId":"9e89cf6f","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:26:50.091Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the channel configuration! The output shows:\n\nChat Channels:\n1. **Feishu tts:** configured, enabled\n2. **openclaw-weixin 2be069d50844-im-bot:** configured, enabled\n3. **OpenClawWeChat default:** not configured, enabled\n\nSo the user has:\n- Feishu tts channel (this is the tts account we're on)\n- openclaw-weixin 2be069d50844-im-bot (this might be the KIIT channel or another weixin bot)\n- OpenClawWeChat default (not configured)\n\nThe user mentioned KIIT is another robot. It might be the \"openclaw-weixin 2be069d50844-im-bot\" channel. Or maybe KIIT refers to the WeChat channel.\n\nBut wait - the user's original problem was that the main agent should be on KIIT but got bound to the tts subagent instead. And now I can see the channels list, but I don't see a \"KIIT\" channel explicitly mentioned.\n\nMaybe KIIT is one of these channels. Let me ask the user:\n1. Which of these channels corresponds to KIIT?\n2. How do they want to configure the binding?\n\nActually, looking at the previous agent config:\n- main agent has \"Routing: default (no explicit rules)\"\n- tts agent has \"Routing: Feishu tts\"\n\nSo when a message comes from \"Feishu tts\" channel, it goes to the tts subagent. And main agent has no explicit routing rules, meaning it's the default.\n\nIf they want KIIT to be bound to main, we need to know which channel is KIIT and then configure the routing.\n\nActually wait - looking more carefully at the problem:\n- User said \"主agent main绑定到 KIIT 上\" - main agent should be bound to KIIT\n\n\n- User said \"tts选品助手\" is bound to tts channel\n\nSo the user wants:\n- KIIT channel → main agent\n- tts channel → tts subagent\n\nBut currently the tts channel is correctly routed to the tts subagent. The issue is probably that KIIT channel is either:\n1. Not in the channel list (maybe it's not configured at all)\n2. Incorrectly routed to the wrong agent\n3. Or the routing for main agent is not set up correctly for KIIT\n\nThe user needs to either add KIIT as a new channel or fix the routing so that KIIT maps to the main agent instead of whatever it's currently mapped to. The user needs to clarify which channel corresponds to KIIT and then either set up routing for the main agent to that channel or adjust the existing tts subagent routing. Looking at the configuration, main has no explicit routing rules while tts is already bound to Feishu tts, so if KIIT is a separate channel, the main agent needs explicit routing configured to point to it.","thinkingSignature":"9bed9bf207db8611b801132d4efed85d9d7ef513b13ea3b8e31bd0f6a35b0e12"},{"type":"text","text":"看到了！`openclaw channels list` 显示：\n\n**Chat Channels:**\n- **Feishu tts:** configured, enabled\n- **openclaw-weixin 2be069d50844-im-bot:** configured, enabled\n- **OpenClawWeChat default:** not configured, enabled\n\nKIIT 是这三个里面的哪一个？应该是 **openclaw-weixin** 这个 channel 吧？\n\n如果 KIIT 是 openclaw-weixin channel，那现在它没有显示绑定到哪个 agent。我们需要给 **main** agent 添加一条 routing rule，让 KIIT (openclaw-weixin) 绑定到 main agent。\n\n你确认一下：\n1. KIIT = openclaw-weixin 2be069d50844-im-bot 这个 channel？\n2. 确认后我来帮你改配置，让 main agent 绑定到这个 channel。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":19838,"output":776,"cacheRead":30800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51414,"cost":{"input":0.0059514,"output":0.0009312,"cacheRead":0.0018479999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0087306}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775057193202,"responseId":"061c6c292367132b69ff8db4dcc96554"}}
