{"type":"message","id":"43690e3c","parentId":"8d92a27d","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:28:27.567Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying \"不是那两个都是 微信的\" meaning \"No, those two are both WeChat\" (微信). So:\n- Feishu tts = Feishu (飞书)\n- openclaw-weixin 2be069d50844-im-bot = WeChat\n- OpenClawWeChat default = WeChat\n\nSo none of these is KIIT. KIIT must be a different channel that is not yet configured or not showing in the list. \n\nThe user said KIIT is another robot. Maybe KIIT is a Feishu bot that hasn't been configured yet, or maybe the KIIT channel isn't showing up for some reason.\n\nWait - the user initially said \"主agent main绑定到 KIIT 上\" and \"kiit 机器人已经不说话了\" - meaning the KIIT robot stopped talking. And they wanted to \"bind me back\" to KIIT.\n\nSo KIIT is some kind of channel/robot that should be connected but isn't working properly. Since it's not showing in the channels list, maybe:\n1. KIIT is a Feishu bot that needs to be configured/connected\n2. Or the KIIT configuration is missing/broken\n\nSince the user said KIIT should be bound to main agent, and it's not showing up in the channels list, maybe the KIIT channel needs to be set up first.\n\nI should ask the user what KIIT is - is it a Feishu bot? A different platform? And whether they need to add/configure the KIIT channel.","thinkingSignature":"1101f4621bcb34f8f2ba0e3537ff98bc9bfb27983fad385c2022dabe58a020c4"},{"type":"text","text":"哦，明白了！那两个（Feishu tts）和 openclaw-weixin 是不同的平台：\n\n- **Feishu tts** = 飞书\n- **openclaw-weixin** = 微信（2个）\n- **OpenClawWeChat default** = 微信（未配置）\n\n所以 **KIIT** 不在这三个里面。KIIT 是哪个平台的机器人？是飞书的吗？还是其他平台？\n\n如果 KIIT 是飞书机器人但没显示在列表里，可能需要先配置/添加 KIIT 这个 channel。你知道 KIIT 是哪个平台的吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109,"output":437,"cacheRead":49584,"cacheWrite":2022,"totalTokens":52152,"cost":{"input":0.000032699999999999995,"output":0.0005244,"cacheRead":0.0029750399999999995,"