{"type":"message","id":"1288e2bc","parentId":"1ddd5816","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:41:54.090Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the openclaw.json configuration now. I can see:\n\n1. `bindings` array shows:\n```json\n\"bindings\": [\n  {\n    \"agentId\": \"tts\",\n    \"match\": {\n      \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n      \"accountId\": \"tts\"\n    }\n  }\n]\n```\n\nSo the binding maps the feishu tts channel to the tts agent.\n\n2. There's no binding for the main agent - it says \"routing: default (no explicit rules)\" in the agents list.\n\n3. The issue is that the user wants KIIT to be bound to main agent, but I don't see KIIT anywhere in the config.\n\n4. Looking at the `tools` section:\n```json\n\"tools\": {\n  \"profile\": \"coding\",\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nThe exec security is probably set at a different level. Looking at the gateway section:\n```json\n\"gateway\": {\n  ...\n  \"tools\": {\n    \"allow\": [\n      \"*\"\n    ]\n  },\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nThis shows `tools.allow: [\"*\"]` which should allow all tools. But there's also a `nodes` section with denyCommands.\n\nActually, looking at the system prompt error message earlier:\n```\nContext: provider=feishu session=agent=tts:feishu:direct:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\nFix-it keys:\n- tools.elevated.enabled\n- tools.elevated.allowFrom.<provider>\n- agents.list[].tools.elevated.enabled\n- agents.list[].tools.elevated.allowFrom.<provider>\n```\n\nSo the fix needs to be in `agents.list[].tools.elevated`. The current agents don't have this setting.\n\nThe user said I need to change something to \"full\" in openclaw.json. Looking at the config, I don't see a \"security\" or \"exec\" section with \"full\" mode. \n\nI need to add `tools.elevated.enabled: true` to the tts agent configuration. Since I'm running as the tts agent in this Feishu session, enabling elevated exec for that agent would allow me to execute commands directly. The user probably knows exactly which setting needs to change - they mentioned something about setting it to \"full\" which likely refers to enabling elevated permissions for this specific agent. Looking at the tool permissions, the `feishu_im_*` tools are already listed in `alsoAllow`, but exec requires elevated privileges. I should try enabling elevated execution for the tts agent by adding the appropriate configuration flag to its tools section, or possibly at the global level if that's where it needs to be set.","thinkingSignature":"26b2906b1a58f9f372ec77fc57a235fe55c0bb9907ac4891061331366f0cd321"},{"type":"text","text":"找到了！我看到配置了。问题是 **exec 需要 elevated 权限**，而当前配置里没有开启。\n\n你需要在你自己的终端里修改 `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`，在 `agents.list` 里找到 **tts** agent，添加 `tools.elevated` 配置：\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"tts\",\n  \"name\": \"TTS-选品专家\",\n  \"workspace\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace-selector\",\n  \"agentDir\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/agent\",\n  \"tools\": {\n    \"elevated\": {\n      \"enabled\": true\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n或者也可以在全局 `tools` 下面加 `elevated: { enabled: true }`。\n\n你自己改一下 openclaw.json，然后重启 OpenClaw，我就能直接执行命令了，不用每次审批。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":33469,"output":747,"cacheRead":30800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65016,"cost":{"input":0.0100407,"output":0.0008964,"cacheRead":0.0018479999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0127851}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775058091400,"responseId":"061c6fabd0854ff79f3aed07d6eac01a"}}
