{"type":"message","id":"2f219abc","parentId":"b906292d","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:54:03.197Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1j8w5nwul8bb_1","toolName":"image","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This screenshot shows a web-based administration panel, likely for an AI agent framework or orchestration tool called \"openclaw\" (based on the workspace file path). The interface is in a dark theme and uses a mix of English and Chinese.\n\nHere is a detailed breakdown of the configuration options and settings visible:\n\n### **1. Navigation and Context (Left Sidebar)**\nThe sidebar indicates the various management sections of the tool. The section currently selected is **\"代理\" (Agent)**.\n*   **Top-level items:** Chat, Control, Overview, Channels, Instances, Sessions, Usage, Cron Jobs.\n*   **Agent sub-menu:** The current view is within the \"Agent\" category, which includes sub-links for:\n    *   **代理 (Agent)** - The current page being viewed.\n    *   **技能 (Skills)**\n    *   **节点 (Nodes)**\n*   **Bottom items:** Settings and Documents.\n\n### **2. Workspace Selector (Top Center)**\nA red box highlights a dropdown menu for selecting different workspaces or agent identities.\n*   The current selection is **`main (default)`**.\n*   The dropdown is open, showing one other option: **`TTS-选品专家` (TTS Selection Expert)**.\n*   Next to this selector, there are tabs for **Channels (3)** and **Cron Jobs**.\n\n### **3. Overview Section**\nThis section provides metadata for the selected workspace:\n*   **Workspace Path:** `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace` (indicates a Linux-based local file system path).\n*   **Primary Model:** Summarizes the current selection as `minimax/MiniMax-M2.7 (+2 fallback)`.\n*   **Skills Filter:** Set to **`all skills`**. This is the closest setting to a \"full\" capability setting visible on this screen.\n*   **Unsaved Changes Warning:** A text prompt warns \"You have unsaved config changes.\"\n\n### **4. Model Selection Section**\nThis area defines which AI models the agent will use:\n*   **Primary model (default):** A dropdown menu currently set to **`Minimax (minimax/MiniMax-M2.7)`**.\n*   **Fallbacks:** Shows a list of backup models to use if the primary fails. Currently, two are selected: **`openrouter/auto`** and **`openrouter/free`**.\n\n### **5. Action Buttons (Bottom)**\n*   **Reload Config:** A button to refresh settings from the source.\n*   **Save:** A prominent red button to commit the unsaved configuration changes.\n\n### **Search for Specific Keywords**\nPer your request, I searched for settings related to \"full,\" \"security,\" or \"exec\":\n*   **\"Full\":** No explicit \"full\" toggle is visible. However, under \"Overview,\" the **\"Skills Filter\" is set to \"all skills,\"** which likely grants the agent full access to its programmed capabilities.\n*   **\"Security\":** No settings or mentions of security, permissions, or access control are visible on this specific screen.\n*   **\"Exec\":** No settings related to execution environments, code execution, or \"exec\" commands are visible here. These settings might exist under the \"Nodes\" or \"Settings\" sections in the sidebar."}],"details":{"model":"minimax/MiniMax-VL-01","image":"/home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/d5c3a901-6527-4a29-a7f8-beee73131108.jpg","attempts":[]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775058843193}}
{"type":"message","id":"fa8f852c","parentId":"2f219abc","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:54:18.427Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The image analysis shows the OpenClaw dashboard. It seems like the user is showing me two agents:\n1. main (default)\n2. TTS-选品专家\n\nAnd they're asking which one to change to full. The image shows the \"Skills Filter\" is set to \"all skills\" which might be the \"full\" setting the user is referring to.\n\nBut actually, looking at the dashboard, I don't see a clear \"full\" option. Maybe the user meant a different setting. The \"Skills Filter: all skills\" could be what they're referring to as \"full\" - meaning all skills are available.\n\nBut the real question is about exec permissions. Looking back at the context, the issue is that I (as the tts agent) can't execute commands without approval. The user said they changed something to \"full\" but it didn't work.\n\nWait - the user said \"后台有两个agent ， 你要把那个改成full\" - they're saying there are two agents in the backend and I need to change one to full. But from the image, I can see the workspace selector shows main and TTS-选品专家. Which one should be set to full?\n\nLooking at the error message earlier:\n```\nContext: provider=feishu session=agent=tts:feishu:direct:ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68\nFix-it keys:\n- tools.elevated.enabled\n- tools.elevated.allowFrom.<provider>\n- agents.list[].tools.elevated.enabled\n- agents.list[].tools.elevated.allowFrom.<provider>\n```\n\nSo I need to enable elevated for the tts agent specifically. The user is showing me the dashboard where I can see both agents, and asking which one to change.\n\nActually, I think the issue is that I need to look at the actual openclaw.json config file again to see what the user changed. \n\nI should ask the user to clarify which agent they're referring to, or maybe just have them show me the config file directly so I can see what was changed.","thinkingSignature":"b867c2ae6da12ce2f0646c2da31c2ccb86ca2bd4cfeabd91ab614c494ac95920"},{"type":"text","text":"看到了！图片里显示的是 OpenClaw 的控制面板，里面有两个 agent：\n1. **main (default)**\n2. **TTS-选品专家**\n\n你问要把哪个改成 full。从错误信息看，我需要给 **tts** 这个 agent 开启 `tools.elevated.enabled`。\n\n不过图片里没显示 exec 相关的设置选项。你说的 \"full\" 是指什么？是 `Skills Filter` 改成 `all skills` 吗？还是在别的地方看到的设置？\n\n另外，你之前在 openclaw.json 里改的哪个字段？我想确认一下你改的位置对不对。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":15197,"output":557,"cacheRead":31228,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46982,"cost":{"input":0.0045591,"output":0.0006684,"cacheRead":0.0018736799999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0071011799999999995}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775058843198,"responseId":"061c729b3b6d7d957967647bc629cc24"}}
