{"type":"message","id":"493a3820","parentId":"bfd89008","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:55:26.951Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying they enabled \"全部工具\" (all tools) - this likely means they set the Skills Filter to \"all skills\" as I suspected from the image. But this doesn't help with the exec approval issue - \"all tools\" doesn't mean exec doesn't need approval.\n\nThe problem is that exec needs elevated permissions. The error message mentioned:\n- tools.elevated.enabled\n- tools.elevated.allowFrom.<provider>\n\nMaybe the setting is in the agent's config in openclaw.json. Let me look at the current config again. I already read it earlier. I need to find where to add `tools.elevated` for the tts agent.\n\nActually, maybe the user changed something in the dashboard (the UI) not the json file directly. Let me think about this...\n\nThe exec approval issue is because of the gateway's security policy. Looking at the error:\n```\nApproval required (id xxx, full xxx-xxx-...)\nMode: foreground (interactive approvals available).\n```\n\nThe mode is \"foreground (interactive approvals available)\" which means it needs approval every time. For exec to work without approval, I would need either:\n1. The gateway to have exec security set to \"full\" or \"allowlist\" with the right entries\n2. The agent to have elevated exec permissions\n\nBut looking at the config I read earlier, I don't see a global exec security setting. \n\nLet me think about what else could help. Maybe the user is saying they enabled \"all tools\" in the skills filter in the dashboard. But that doesn't affect exec permissions.\n\nActually wait - maybe the setting the user is referring to IS in the dashboard for the agent itself. Let me look at the tts agent's workspace is `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace-selector`. The agentDir is `/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/agent`.\n\nMaybe there's a local config file inside the agent's directory that controls exec permissions?\n\nLet me ask the user to check if there's an openclaw.json inside the agent's directory, or maybe they need to add elevated permissions to the tts agent in openclaw.json specifically.\n\n\nThe user might be referring to \"全部工具\" in the context of the tool permissions in openclaw.json - there's a `tools.alsoAllow` list that might need adjustment. But that doesn't control exec. Let me just ask them directly what they changed and where, since I can't see their screen to know exactly what \"full\" setting they enabled.","thinkingSignature":"201942fbfa08309cf6dd9f52d1d17b2b82c7cc48b4de3f46fc93cfc3ce5f07ab"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\"全部工具\"（所有工具）开启的是 Skills Filter，这个不影响 exec 审批。\n\nExec 需要的是 **elevated 权限**，在 openclaw.json 里需要这样改：\n\n```json\n{\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"list\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"tts\",\n        \"name\": \"TTS-选品专家\",\n        \"workspace\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace-selector\",\n        \"agentDir\": \"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/tts/agent\",\n        \"tools\": {\n          \"elevated\": {\n            \"enabled\": true,\n            \"allowFrom\": [\"feishu\"]\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n你在 dashboard 里看到 tts agent 的配置里有 `Elevated Exec` 或者类似的选项吗？可能需要在那儿开启，不是 Skills Filter。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":140,"output":687,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":52511,"totalTokens":53338,"cost":{"input":0.000042,"output":0.0008244,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.019691625,"total":0.020558025}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775058906169,"responseId":"061c72da7cc3eee61e8b1b4c2ae21596"}}
