{"type":"message","id":"de277617","parentId":"03cd0ccb","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:58:15.150Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ws999p6m8s4d_1","toolName":"image","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the screenshot provided, the interface is a management dashboard for an AI agent, specifically within a section labeled **\"Tools\"** under the **\"Agent\"** (代理) category in the sidebar.\n\nHere is a detailed breakdown of the settings related to permissions and tool access:\n\n### 1. Tool Access Overview\nThis section serves as the primary permission control center for the agent's capabilities.\n\n*   **Profile Dropdown:** Currently set to **`full`**. This is likely a high-level permission set. Changing this dropdown would presumably switch between different predefined permission tiers (e.g., restricted, basic, full).\n*   **Source Field:** Displays **`agent override`**. This indicates that the current permissions for this specific agent are overriding any global or default settings.\n*   **Enabled Status:** A text indicator states **\"73/73 enabled.\"** This suggests there are 73 individual capabilities or tools available to the system, and this specific agent has permission to use all of them.\n*   **Global Toggles (Buttons):**\n    *   **Enable All / Disable All:** These buttons allow for bulk management of permissions, either granting the agent access to every available tool or stripping all access at once.\n    *   **Reload Config:** Likely refreshes the permission settings from the underlying configuration files.\n    *   **Save:** Commits any changes made to the profile or individual tool toggles.\n\n### 2. Built-in Tools (Command Execution & Permissions)\nWhile there is no single \"exec\" toggle, the \"Built-in tools\" section lists specific capabilities that represent different types of command or action execution permissions:\n\n*   **Agents Tool:** Describes the ability to \"List OpenClaw agent ids you can target with 'sessions spawn'...\" This indicates permission to spawn and control other sub-processes or agents.\n*   **Cron Tool:** Controls \"Schedule and manage cron jobs...\" This grants the agent permission to execute tasks automatically based on time intervals, which is a form of persistent command execution.\n*   **Edit Tool:** Describes the ability to \"Edit a single file using exact text.\" This is a high-level permission related to filesystem access and modification.\n*   **Canvas Tool:** Relates to \"Control node canvases,\" representing permissions to interact with a visual or structural UI element of the system.\n\n### 3. Sidebar Context (Permissions/Security)\nThe sidebar on the left (in Chinese) provides further context for security-related management:\n\n*   **实例 (Instances):** Likely manages the active environments where code/commands are running.\n*   **定时任务 (Scheduled Tasks / Cron Jobs):** A dedicated section for managing the execution of recurring commands.\n*   **代理 (Agent):** The currently selected tab, where granular tool permissions are managed.\n\n### Summary of Command Execution Controls\nIn this interface, command execution permissions are not handled by a single \"elevated\" toggle. Instead, they are managed through:\n1.  **The \"Profile\" dropdown** (set to `full`), which acts as a broad security clearance.\n2.  **Granular Tool Access**, where specific capabilities like file editing (`Edit`), process spawning (`Agents`), and task scheduling (`Cron`) can be enabled or disabled individually or in bulk."}],"details":{"model":"minimax/MiniMax-VL-01","image":"/home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/6f746fc4-7a4e-4e29-ba03-cc151de92bef.jpg","attempts":[]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775059095142}}
{"type":"message","id":"9ed44837","parentId":"de277617","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:58:23.125Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see! The screenshot shows that under the Tools section for the agent, there's a \"Profile\" dropdown set to \"full\". This is what the user is referring to! The user set the Tools profile to \"full\" which should enable all tools including exec.\n\nBut the exec is still asking for approval. Maybe the issue is that:\n1. The profile needs to be saved and the gateway needs to be restarted\n2. Or maybe there's a different setting needed for exec specifically\n\nThe user seems to have found the right place - the Tools section with Profile set to \"full\". But exec is still asking for approval. Let me suggest they try saving and reloading, or check if there's a specific exec permission.","thinkingSignature":"df1c88d8a533b677ba4a9692877896079adf7f57d2faa4b233f65ab46fd45fc7"},{"type":"text","text":"看到了！你已经把 **Profile** 改成 `full` 了！这就是\"全部工具\"的设置。\n\n但是 exec 可能需要单独再授权。你滚动往下看，有没有看到 **Exec** 相关的选项？或者点 **Enable All** 按钮试试？\n\n另外，改完设置后要点 **Save**，然后可能需要 **Reload Config** 或者重启 OpenClaw。\n\n你试试先点 **Enable All**（如果还没点过），然后 Save，看看 exec 还需不需要审批。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":18225,"output":243,"cacheRead":36414,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54882,"cost":{"input":0.0054675,"output":0.0002916,"cacheRead":0.00218484,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00794394}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775059095151,"responseId":"061c73973924946141d6da6a110c787d"}}
